Lecture series with thematic lectures in three blocks (theoretical topics, practical topics and practical work) which form a cross-section of everyday museum work and help give a wider perspective on one of the most important preservers of cultural heritage.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To provide an overview of contemporary research topics in museuology, the history of museums, the role of museums and their function in society today; analysis of  collection and  preservation politics;  documentation and description of museal objects.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon successful completion of the course,students should:  have an overview of museology and its specifics; be familiar with the main historical developmental trends of museums; know the basics of  documenting and cataloguing museum objects;be able to describe museum objects; be able to find relevant information on the specialty; value cultural heritage.
